stateDiagram-v2

    [*] --> Drafted

    Drafted     : title written; pre-release design review against documented conventions
    Beta        : private alpha or controlled beta with design partners; breaking changes expected
    GA          : public release; full support; recommended version
    Maintenance : security and high-severity bug fixes only; no new features
    Deprecated  : Sunset announced; T-12, T-6, T-3, T-1 month reminders; migration tooling published
    Retired     : 410 Gone responses; routes removed; code deleted; infrastructure destroyed

    Drafted     --> Beta        : design + review complete
    Beta        --> GA          : design partners validated
    GA          --> Maintenance : next major version reaches GA
    Maintenance --> Deprecated  : Sunset announcement
    Deprecated  --> Retired     : binding sunset date arrived

    Retired --> [*]

    note right of Maintenance
        Multi-version coexistence:
        when this version enters
        Maintenance, the next major
        version (vN+1) enters its
        own GA on a parallel track.
        Both versions live in
        production simultaneously,
        bounded by the announced
        sunset date.
    end note

    note right of Deprecated
        Deprecation discipline:
        Sunset HTTP header on every
        response; minimum 12-24
        month notice (public) or
        shorter (internal); reminder
        cadence T-12, T-6, T-3, T-1
        months; identified consumers
        receive direct outreach;
        migration tooling published
        alongside announcement.
    end note

    note right of Retired
        Retirement actually executes:
        sunset date is binding; routes
        return 410 Gone with migration
        documentation in response;
        code deleted from source repo
        after grace period;
        infrastructure destroyed last.
    end note
